# apps (and how it have to work) – Expanded

## 1. apps list and their structure

- **Description:** Define the structure, behavior, and visual design of each app module inside the OS. Each app lives in its own folder under `/apps`, has a main entry file, optional assets (icons, images), and exports a React component that the OS Window Manager can render dynamically.

### terminal [x](but can be improved a lot to add more commands and features and redesign the UI)

- **difficulty:** easy
- **Description:** A command-line interface (CLI) that allows users to execute basic commands in the OS simulation.
- **Functionality:**
  - Execute commands: `ls`, `cd`, `echo`, `cat`
  - Display command output in scrollable console
  - Handle keyboard input (enter, arrow navigation for command history)
  - Optional: auto-completion and error handling
- **Integration:**
  - Registers itself in the App Registry
  - Interacts with the Process Manager to simulate creating a new process
  - Can open other apps via commands (e.g., `open calculator`)
- **Style:**
  - Dark background (`#1E1E2F`)
  - Green monospaced text (`#00FF7F`)
  - Soft inset shadow around the terminal window for depth
  - Scrollable terminal area with neumorphic scrollbar

### system info

- **difficulty:** easy-medium
- **Description:** Displays real-time system metrics such as CPU usage, memory usage, running processes, and allows basic process management.
- **Functionality:**
  - Show live CPU, RAM, and storage usage charts
  - List active processes with CPU/memory footprint
  - Kill processes via interface
  - Expand to full-screen view on launch for better readability
- **Integration:**
  - Registered in App Registry
  - Fetches live data from Process Manager
- **Style:**
  - Clean neumorphic cards for metrics
  - Interactive charts (Framer Motion animated)
  - Buttons with Extruded shadows for actions (kill process, refresh)

### portfolio [x]

- **difficulty:** hard
- **Description:** Showcases all projects in a modular interactive format, including images, descriptions, links, and tags.
- **Functionality:**
  - Dynamic project cards with hover animations
  - Clickable for detailed modal or new app window
  - Filter projects by technology, type, or status
- **Integration:**
  - Registered in App Registry
  - Fetches project data from JSON or Markdown files
- **Style:**
  - Neumorphic cards with subtle hover lift
  - Smooth Framer Motion transitions for modals
  - Consistent iconography and typography

### resume

- **difficulty:** hard
- **Description:** Interactive, timeline-based resume with clickable sections.
- **Functionality:**
  - Sections for experience, education, skills
  - Expand/collapse for details
  - Downloadable PDF export option
- **Integration:**
  - OS windowed interface
- **Style:**
  - Vertical timeline with neumorphic "pillowed" cards
  - Accent color for skill highlights and links

### docs [x]

- **difficulty:** easy
- **Description:** Viewer for project documentation files in `/docs` folder.
- **Functionality:**
  - Navigate folders (`Style`, `Roadmap`)
  - Render Markdown files dynamically
  - Full-screen toggle for better readability
- **Integration:**
  - Reads from `/docs` folder and renders content
- **Style:**
  - Light neumorphic panels for each doc
  - Table of contents on the left sidebar
  - Smooth scrolling with floating shadows

### blog [x]

- **difficulty:** easy
- **Description:** Personal blog reader for posts stored in Markdown or fetched from CMS.
- **Functionality:**
  - List recent posts with title, date, snippet
  - Click to open full post in modal or new window
  - Search/filter posts
- **Integration:**
  - Fetch Markdown content or API
- **Style:**
  - Neumorphic cards with hover lift
  - Accent color for links
  - Smooth animated transitions

### contact [x](but can be improved a lot)

- **difficulty:** easy
- **Description:** Contact form and personal info viewer.
- **Functionality:**
  - Form submission with validation
  - Display email, phone, social links
  - Optional: integrate with API for email sending
- **Integration:**
  - Standalone OS app, registers in App Registry
- **Style:**
  - Input fields with `Inset Deep` shadows
  - Submit button with lift animation
  - Clean layout with padding and spacing

### AI agent

- **difficulty:** hard
- **Description:** AI assistant that answers questions about projects, portfolio, and system usage.
- **Functionality:**
  - Reads `docs/project` and `docs/maivand/info.json` for context
  - Can answer questions about projects and personal portfolio
  - Opens other apps on command (e.g., `open terminal`)
- **Integration:**
  - Connected to OpenRouter model
  - Registered in App Registry
  - Uses Project Context Loader to pre-load documents
- **Style:**
  - Chat interface with neumorphic message bubbles
  - Floating assistant icon in OS dock
  - Typing animation and smooth message appearance

### calculator [x]

- **difficulty:** easy
- **Description:** Simple calculator app with basic operations.
- **Functionality:**
  - Add, subtract, multiply, divide
  - Keyboard and click input
  - Memory operations optional
- **Integration:**
  - OS windowed interface
- **Style:**
  - Buttons with `Extruded` shadow
  - Rounded edges and smooth hover effect
  - Neumorphic display area for input/output

### notes [x]

- **difficulty:** easy
- **Description:** Note-taking application with simple CRUD functionality.
- **Functionality:**
  - Create, edit, delete notes
  - Categorize or tag notes
  - Save notes locally (localStorage/IndexedDB)
- **Integration:**
  - Registers in App Registry
- **Style:**
  - Soft inset cards for each note
  - Smooth drag-and-drop reorder
  - Floating "new note" button with neumorphic lift

### weather

- **difficulty:** medium
- **Description:** Displays weather forecasts for selected locations.
- **Functionality:**
  - Show current conditions and 5-day forecast
  - Weather icons and animations
  - Search cities and set default location
- **Integration:**
  - Fetches data from weather API
- **Style:**
  - Rounded neumorphic cards for each day
  - Animated icon for weather condition
  - Subtle shadow and background elevation for depth

### clock [x](but can be improved a lot)

- **difficulty:** easy
- **Description:** World clock displaying multiple timezones.
- **Functionality:**
  - Add/remove cities
  - Toggle between 12h/24h format
  - Alarm optional
- **Integration:**
  - OS windowed interface
- **Style:**
  - Circular neumorphic clock face
  - Smooth ticking animation
  - Soft inset for numbers and hands
